    <briefdescription>
<para>Lightweight handle for reading messages from a <ref refid="classhelios_1_1core_1_1container_1_1buffer_1_1TypeIndexedDoubleBuffer" kindref="compound">TypeIndexedDoubleBuffer</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1core_1_1container_1_1buffer_1_1TypeIndexedDoubleBuffer_1_1ReadSource" kindref="compound">ReadSource</ref> provides a focused interface for message consumers that only need read access. It holds a non-owning pointer to a <ref refid="classhelios_1_1core_1_1container_1_1buffer_1_1TypeIndexedDoubleBuffer" kindref="compound">TypeIndexedDoubleBuffer</ref> and exposes only the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1core_1_1container_1_1buffer_1_1TypeIndexedDoubleBuffer_1_1ReadSource_1ada94a4a83f08d72994e14a6d3b821e88" kindref="member">read()</ref> operation.</para>
<para>This class is useful for dependency injection where systems should be able to consume messages without having access to buffer management operations. </para>
